The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Timeout

 DRAMA

 December 11 at Academy of Fine Arts; 3.30 pm: Sansriti presents Phataru. Direction: Debesh Chattopadhyay. 

 December 11 at Girish Mancha; 3.30 pm: Sundaram presents Operation Bhomragarh. Drama, direction and acting: Manoj Mitra. 

 December 11 at Sarat Sadan, Howrah; 6.30 pm: Shouvanik presents Indurkal, based on Agatha Christie?s Mousetrap. Dir: Asit Ghosh. 

 December 12 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.30 pm: Mangalik presents Haroon-al Rashid. Dir: Samir Biswas. 

 December 12 at Girish Mancha; 6.30 pm: Nandikar presents Sojon Badiyar Ghaat. Direction: Goutam Halder. 

 December 12 at Madhusudan Mancha; 6.30 pm: Kalyani Natyacharcha Kendra presents Khwabnama. Direction: Kishore Sengupta. 

 December 13 at Gyan Manch; 6.30 pm: Theatrecian presents a JUDE production, Shakespeare?s Measure For Measure. Direction: Ananda Lal. 

 EXHIBITION

 Till December 21 (except Mondays) at Birla Academy of Art amp; Culture; 4 pm - 8 pm: Ray?s Cinema Away From Cinema ? a collection of posters, lobby cards, booklets and original drawings and sketches of Satyajit Ray and Sandip Ray. 

 Till December 11 at Gallery Kanishka?s; 11 am - 8 pm: Artisans? Art Works ? an exhibition of dokra crafts made by craftspeople of West Bengal. 

 ART

 December 11, 4 pm - 9 pm; December 12, 12 noon - 9 pm at The Hiland Park, Clubhouse ?County? (opp. Peerless Hospital): Craetive Strokes presents an exhibition cum sale of a rare collection of Indian art created by over 100 budding artists of Bengal. A certain percentage collected from sales will go towards orphanages and old age homes. 

 Till December 12 at Vikalp Art Shop, Swabhumi; 2 pm - 8 pm: Vikalp Art Fair, showcasing 50 young artists at work. 

 Till December 18 at Academy of Fine Arts; 3 pm - 8 pm: Mukta Shilpa presents Contemporary Kolkata through Contemporary Art. Curated by Ratnottama Sengupta. 

 performing artS

 December 11 at Kanan Sangeet Kunj, CK 122 Salt Lake, Sector II (near Tank no. 9); 5 pm: An evening of Hindustani classical music in memory of Pandit A. Kanan. Featuring Shiladitya Banerjee (vocal), Atanu Majumdar (sitar), Sanchaita Chaudhuri (vocal) and Pandit Sohanlal Sharma (harmonium solo). 

 December 11 at Kala Mandir; 6.30 pm: On the 62nd birth anniversary of Ananda Shankar, Ananda Shankar Centre for Performing Arts presents Chirantan ? a tribute to Tagore. Conceptualised and choreographed by Tanusree Shankar, the music has been composed and arranged by Debajyoti Mishra with narration by Amitabh Bachchan. 

 Till December 14 at Rabindra Sadan; 6 pm: Uday Shankar Dance Festival 2004, organised by Paschimbanga Rajya Sangeet Academy and West Bengal Dance Group Federation. Today: Srinwanti Chakraborty (Odissi), Kabita Chatterjee, Sudipta Hore and Sangita Sarkhel (Bharata Natyam in trio), Susmita Chatterjee Sur (Kathak) and Romakanta Sen amp; party (Mayurbhanj Chhau). 

 December 12 at Academy of Fine Arts; 10 am: Samskar Bharati presents a programme of Bengali traditional Kathakata, Madhur, a solo recital by Anandi Basu, and a short play, Mr. Tension, directed by Amit De. 

 TALK

 December 11 at the Ramakrishna Vedanta Math, 19A amp; B Raja Rajkrishna Street; 7 pm: Swami Paramatmananda will speak in Bengali on Manusher Divya-Swarup. 

 December 12 at G.D. Birla Sabhagar; 11 am: Professor P. Lal reads of Vyasa?s disappointment at his son Dhritarastra?s refusal to order Duryodhana to withdraw his army, and Sanjaya?s elaborate account of the glory of Bharata-varsa doomed to perish if the battle takes place, in the 256th weekly session of his complete English transcreation of Vyasa?s Mahabharata. 

 SEMINAR

 December 11 at HSBC Hall, Tolly Club; 6 pm: Bharathidasan Institute of Management, Tiruchirapalli Alumni Association - Calcutta Chapter presents a seminar on history and management, titled War and Peace (An evening in past, an evening for future). Entry by invitation only. Details with Abhishek Kumar, . 

 BOOK RELEASE

 December 13 at Seagull Bookstore, 31A S.P. Mukherjee Road; 7 pm: The Seagull Foundation for the Arts and International Workgroup for Indigenous Affairs, Copenhagen host the release of Development and Ethnocide: Colonial Practices in the Andaman Islands by Sita Venkateswar. The author will read excerpts from the book and share her experiences. 

 IN MEMORIAM

 December 12 at 12A Golf Towers, 9 Prince Gholam Mohammad Shah Road; 4 pm: The devotees of Sri Gouranga Ashram will pay homage to the founder-acharya, His Divine Grace Om Vishnupad 108 Tridandi Swami Sri Srimat Bhakti Sravan Tirtha Goswami Maharaj, who left for his heavenly abode on December 1. 

 MEDICAL

 December 13 at the seminar hall, Institute of Psychiatry, IPGME amp;R, SSKM Hospital; 12.30 pm: On the eve of World Epilepsy Day, Indian Epilepsy Association (West Bengal Chapter) organises an awareness programme for the epilepsy patients and their parents, guardians and caregivers. There will be active and comprehensive interaction between neurologists and the caregivers. 

